ot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="wasted food" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-750x506.png" data-large-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-1090x735.png" /></a></p>几乎一半的浪费食物来自家庭，其中几乎一半......<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/food/" rel="tag">食品</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/garbage/" rel="tag">垃圾</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/methane/" rel="tag">甲烷</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/reuters/" rel="tag">路透社</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2023/08/09/greenhouse-gas-from-wasting-food-at-home/"><img width="750" height="506" src="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-750x506.png" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-750x506.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-1090x735.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-210x142.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-768x518.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-1536x1035.png 1536w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-2048x1381.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" data-attachment-id="71836" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2023/08/09/greenhouse-gas-from-wasting-food-at-home/wasted-food/" data-orig-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food.png" data-orig-size="2409,1624" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="wasted food" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-750x506.png" data-large-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/wasted-food-1090x735.png" /></a></p><p>几乎一半的浪费食物来自家庭，其中近一半进入垃圾填埋场。腐烂的食物会产生甲烷。艾莉·J·莱文 (Ally J. Levine) 和黛西·钟 (Daisy Chung) 为路透社解释了<a href="https://www.reuters.com/graphics/FOOD-WASTE/METHANE/gdpzwqwqovw/">为什么这是一个问题，以及为什么我们应该尽量减少丢弃的食物量</a>：</p><blockquote><p>食物在垃圾填埋场分解产生的甲烷占所有人类温室气体排放量的 1.6%。虽然这听起来可能不多，但对于这种特定污染物来说，这个比例很大。 Karl 说，当科学家研究超特定类别时，超过 1% 的任何值都是重要的。</p><p> “任何能够防止食物垃圾未经处理堆积起来的行动都将直接减少对气候的影响。”</p></blockquote><p>我很欣赏那些使数据不那么抽象的插图，这已成为路透社图形的标准。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/food/" rel="tag">食品</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/garbage/" rel="tag">垃圾</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/methane/" rel="tag">甲烷</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/reuters/" rel="tag">路透社</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 71835 </post-id></item></channel></rss><!-- *´¨)
